# Accessibility Patterns

## Core Principles

1. **Semantic HTML**

   - Use proper HTML elements for their intended purpose
   - Implement ARIA landmarks for page structure
   - Follow document outline and heading hierarchy
   - Organize content logically and meaningfully

2. **ARIA Implementation**

   - Use ARIA roles only when HTML semantics aren't sufficient
   - Maintain ARIA states for interactive elements
   - Implement ARIA properties for enhanced context
   - Configure live regions for dynamic content

3. **Keyboard Navigation**

   - Ensure all interactive elements are focusable
   - Implement logical tab order
   - Provide keyboard shortcuts for common actions
   - Handle focus management in modals and popups

4. **Visual Design**

   - Maintain sufficient color contrast (WCAG 2.1 AA)
   - Support different text sizes and zoom levels
   - Design focus indicators for interactive elements
   - Consider reduced motion preferences

## Implementation

### 1. Page Structure

```typescript
export function Layout({ children }: LayoutProps) {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen">
      <SkipLink href="#main">Skip to main content</SkipLink>

      <header role="banner">
        <nav role="navigation" aria-label="Main">
          <MainNav />
        </nav>
      </header>

      <main id="main" role="main" tabIndex={-1}>
        {children}
      </main>

      <footer role="contentinfo">
        <FooterContent />
      </footer>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 2. Interactive Components

```typescript
export function Button({
  children,
  isLoading,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      {...props}
      disabled={isLoading || props.disabled}
      aria-busy={isLoading}
      className={cn(
        'inline-flex items-center justify-center',
        isLoading && 'cursor-wait opacity-50',
        props.className
      )}
    >
      {isLoading && (
        <Spinner
          className="mr-2 h-4 w-4"
          aria-hidden="true"
        />
      )}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

### 3. Form Controls

```typescript
export function FormField({
  label,
  error,
  required,
  children,
}: FormFieldProps) {
  const id = useId();
  const errorId = useId();

  return (
    <div className="space-y-2">
      <Label
        htmlFor={id}
        className={cn(required && 'after:content-["*"] after:ml-1 after:text-destructive')}
      >
        {label}
      </Label>
      {React.Children.map(children, (child) => {
        if (!React.isValidElement(child)) return child;
        return React.cloneElement(child, {
          id,
          'aria-describedby': error ? errorId : undefined,
          'aria-invalid': !!error,
          'aria-required': required,
        });
      })}
      {error && (
        <p
          id={errorId}
          className="text-sm text-destructive"
          role="alert"
        >
          {error}
        </p>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 4. Dialog Management

```typescript
export function Dialog({
  title,
  description,
  children,
  ...props
}: DialogProps) {
  return (
    <DialogPrimitive.Root {...props}>
      <DialogPrimitive.Portal>
        <DialogPrimitive.Overlay
          className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/50"
          aria-hidden="true"
        />
        <DialogPrimitive.Content
          className="fixed left-1/2 top-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"
          aria-labelledby="dialog-title"
          aria-describedby="dialog-description"
        >
          <h2 id="dialog-title" className="text-lg font-bold">
            {title}
          </h2>
          {description && (
            <p id="dialog-description" className="text-muted-foreground">
              {description}
            </p>
          )}
          {children}
          <DialogPrimitive.Close
            aria-label="Close"
            className="absolute right-4 top-4"
          >
            <XIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
          </DialogPrimitive.Close>
        </DialogPrimitive.Content>
      </DialogPrimitive.Portal>
    </DialogPrimitive.Root>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Semantic Structure

- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
- Implement landmarks for major sections
- Provide descriptive labels for regions
- Use lists for related items

### 2. Interactive Elements

- Ensure sufficient touch targets (44x44px)
- Provide visible focus indicators
- Support both mouse and keyboard interaction
- Handle touch and gesture events

### 3. Forms and Validation

- Associate labels with form controls
- Provide clear error messages
- Group related form elements
- Indicate required fields

### 4. Dynamic Content

- Announce important updates
- Manage focus during navigation
- Handle loading states
- Provide progress indicators

### 5. Media

- Include alt text for images
- Provide captions for videos
- Support audio descriptions
- Consider transcripts

## Testing

### 1. Automated Testing

- Implement axe-core for automated checks
- Test keyboard navigation
- Verify ARIA attributes
- Check color contrast

### 2. Manual Testing

- Use screen readers
- Test keyboard-only navigation
- Verify focus management
- Check different zoom levels

